item.title: About
item.description: It’s really simple! All you have to do is find your congressional district and then you’ll see the candidates! Once you see the race, we’ve summarized the answers of the candidates to the top issues that users in that district submitted.

item.title: Contact
item.description: If you have questions or comments, please contact us at jetpackturbo@gmail.com. Thank you for helping us help voters!

item.title: Washington 8th
item.description: This is the Side-by-Side Candidate Comparison Website for Washington State, 8th district. Images Candidates Kim Schrier Justin Greywolf Jesse Jensen Matt Larkin Party Democratic Independent Republican Republican Healthcare Kim Schrier, a pediatrician, is committed to strengthening the healthcare system until every person in this country has access to affordable, high-quality care^1 Justin Greywolf supports a government-funded healthcare system in theory, but doesn’t see it as viable yet. He believes the government should provide healthcare options for those who can’t get it from an employer or on their own, but that insurance coverage shouldn’t be required nor should it be funded through any new or increased taxes ^1 N/A N/A Climate Change Kim Schrier is committed to keeping the air and water clean and transitioning to a clean energy economy to slow the rate of climate change ^1.
